textBox.richText: The Swiss Machine Learning Day aims at bringing together researchers from the Idiap Research Institute and from the École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne working on topics related to machine learning. It is co-organized by François Fleuret and Matthias Seeger. André Anjos and Laurent El-Shafey will be giving a talk entitled “Bob: A Free Library for Reproducible Machine Learning”. For more information the program can be found HERE.
New talk on BOB at the Swiss Machine Learning Day 2013
